Package smarthome.persistence.jpa

Class SensorRepositoryJPAImpl

java.lang.Object
smarthome.persistence.jpa.SensorRepositoryJPAImpl
All Implemented Interfaces:
IRepository<SensorId, Sensor>, ISensorRepository
public class SensorRepositoryJPAImpl extends Object implements ISensorRepository
This class implements the ISensorRepository interface and provides the implementation for the methods defined in the interface. It uses the Java Persistence API (JPA) to interact with the database.

    • findSensorsByDeviceId

      public Iterable<Sensor> findSensorsByDeviceId (DeviceId deviceId)
      Retrieves all Sensor entities associated with a specific device from the database. This method creates a JPA query to select all SensorDataModel entities where the deviceId matches the provided deviceId. The result is then converted to a list of SensorDataModel entities. Finally, the list of SensorDataModel entities is converted to a list of Sensor domain entities using the SensorDataModel's toDomain method.
      Specified by:
      findSensorsByDeviceId in interface ISensorRepository
      Parameters:
      deviceId - The identity of the device whose associated Sensor entities are to be retrieved.
      Returns:
      An Iterable collection containing all Sensor entities associated with the specified device.
